<MudDialog>
    <DialogContent>
        <center>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h4">Code Of Conduct</MudText>
            <br />
            <MudText>
                All participants of PostCarbon events and community, including attendees, performers and organizers are required to agree with the following code of conduct.
            </MudText>
            <br />
            <MudText>
                Please support it and help ensure a safe environment for everybody.
            </MudText>
            <br />
            <br />
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h4">Inclusion </MudText>
            <br />
            <MudText>
                This is a safe space for everyone, irregardless of gender identity and expression, age, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity and religion (or lack thereof).
            </MudText>
            <br />
            <MudText>
                Harassment includes offensive verbal comments related to gender identity and expression, age, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity and religion, as well as deliberate intimidation, stalking, following, disruption of performances, inappropriate physical contact and unwelcome sexual attention.
            </MudText>
            <br />
            <MudText>
                Consent is affirmative, conscious, voluntary, sober and revokable. Under no circumstances will we tolerate harassment in this space.
            </MudText>
            <br />
            <br />
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h4">Guidelines</MudText>
            <br />
            <MudText>
                If you are being harassed, notice that someone else is being harassed or have any other concerns, please reach out to us – we will be in the postcorner.
            </MudText>
            <br />
            <MudText>
                PostCarbon organizers will also be available for issues regarding security or police.
            </MudText>
            <br />
        </center>
    </DialogContent>
</MudDialog>

